“To love is wonderful… but to BE loved…. THAT is truly delicious”. — Donald “Schleppy” Silverman. ❤️ Great words from a wise man.  Rest in peace pal… you were loved by many including me.  Shout out to the entire Silverman fam for taking such good care of him and making him feel delicious.  Poker and performing in South Florida will never be as fun. The last pic is from a couple years ago when he was in the hospital and I FaceTimed him from the shower so he’d have to get well…. so that my naked body wasn’t the last thing he ever saw.  He recovered and kept smiling until 85!  Anyone feeling charitable please consider this cause close to Donald and his family’s heart @2ndnurture

Happy Mothers Day to moms everywhere. This footage was shot on the American side of the Rio Grande River moments after this young mom floated over in a raft.  The local cops let me keep her company while they waited for border patrol to come scoop her up.  It’s a reminder that people will do anything and risk everything to get to our great nation.  Elcy gave birth to her American baby that night.  I hope they’re both still here and living the American dream. ❤️Footage from “Jeff Ross Roasts The Border”) #immigration #border #bordercrossing

social_posts.post_text: #throwback Almost exactly 20 years ago sitting on Saddam’s throne in Baghdad. Former US marine Drew Carey brought a rag tag brigade of comics to entertain troops stationed all over the war zone. It was hot. I was terrified. Our hotel was hit with a mortar attack. I called our mission “Operation Enduring Diarrhea”. Changed my life. 📷: @artistsandathletes #BlakeClark #RockyLaporte #DrewCarey #KyleDunnigan #KathyKinney #AndresFernandez #JeffRoss

Norman Lear was 101 years old and still partying !

After Jada’s infamous Oscars incident I wrote a magazine editorial about my personal experience with alopecia. Norman called me, told me he enjoyed the article, and offered me his hat. 

Once when I told Norman that Gilbert Gottfried was sick he said “Laughing adds time to your life and Gilbert gave me years”. 

Long live King Lear. He added years to our lives. 

Sending love to his friend @carmensandiegola and his family.

Well my old poker pal Norby Walters finally folded. Me, @sarahkatesilverman and @jeffgarlin were the young comics who got invited to play poker with Norby’s pals like Harvey Corman, Jerry Vale, Charles Durning, Sid Caesar and so many other legends.  Buddy Hackett took me over there for the first time. Lots of great stories and free Chinese food.  Norby was in the music biz and is mentioned in a lot of early rap songs. His Oscar parties were epic. Norby kept all the stars humble by repeating his mantra, “Never too big”!
